Choose "Direct" if you wish to connect two computers with a null-modem serial
cable. See the next page for a cable diagram.

Select "Com 1" or "Com 2" depending on which serial port you're using (PC).

If you're playing over a modem, choose the fastest modem baud rate in common
for you and your opponent. If you're playing over a null-modem serial cable,
try the highest speed of 57.6K. If that doesn't work, keep trying the next
highest baud rate until you reach 9600 baud.

If you choose "Modem" for Connection, the second and third screen sections will
appear.

Select "Call" or "Answer" depending on what you and your friend have decided
beforehand.

Choose "Take Over Line" if you wish to dial by hand. The default is "Initiate
Call".

If your modem is not Hayes-compatible or if you wish to enter the modem
commands yourself, select "Special".

If you choose "Standard", you can enter a phone number below. If you choose
"Special", you can enter a direct modem command.

